Dependencies
------------

- Quex version 0.64.8 - http://sourceforge.net/projects/quex/files/HISTORY/0.64/. 
  Follow the installation guide in the quex README
- The mako template system for python
- Clang-format
- boost options
- If you want interactive debugging when code is generated, install IPython

Building
--------

Go into the cpp/ directory and just run make. If you got all the dependencies
install, and you did set QUEX_PATH and the quex executable as said in the quex
readme, it should build.

Testing
-------

Go into the cpp/ directory and run:

$ python tests/driver.py

run:

$ python tests/driver.py -h

For some more help on the driver's command.
